This is our chance to let the government know what's been going on with Fair Use

00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:32.440
and, strangely enough, the date that they are going to cut it off and not let you do the comments anymore and stuff

00:00:32.520 --> 00:00:35.040
is April 1st. April Fools day.

00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:41.540
So I have to emphasize- this is not a April Fools joke. Cross my heart- everything- this is for real!

00:00:41.540 --> 00:00:50.140
This is something every Youtube Creator, every viewer, just anyone that's on the internet, needs to comment on and there's not a lot of time to do it.

00:00:50.140 --> 00:00:57.000
With "Where's the Fair Use?" so many people have verbalized how much the DMCA is being abused with these false claims.

00:00:57.000 --> 00:01:03.080
Everybody has either made a video, or knows somebody that's made a video that, if it went to court, it'd be deemed Fair Use.

00:01:03.080 --> 00:01:04.700
But it was taken down anyway.

00:01:04.700 --> 00:01:11.180
This is your chance to let Washington know, what's going on and how incredibly dated this process is.

00:01:11.280 --> 00:01:16.000
The DMCA was signed into law on October 28th, 1998.

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.980
It was created to protect Copyright holders rights as well as websites who host content.

00:01:20.980 --> 00:01:26.100
If a website gets a DMCA take down, they must take down the content related to the DMCA.

00:01:26.100 --> 00:01:31.200
Here's the problem- it hasn't been updated to account for today's internet.

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:37.300
Back in 1998 the internet was far different. Many big sites were created and many of them failed.

00:01:37.300 --> 00:01:40.640
We backed up our data on floppy disks and we now use the cloud.

00:01:40.640 --> 00:01:46.840
Many of us use the internet for all our entertainment and the DMCA was written for the 1998 internet.

00:01:46.840 --> 00:01:50.620
one of which, a site like Youtube was nothing more than a fantasy.

00:01:50.620 --> 00:01:56.900
News stations aren't the only ones who can break news now- a average person with a cellphone can break the news before they can.

00:01:56.900 --> 00:02:03.260
The internet has changed so much in those 18 years, yet one of the major laws around it has become a fossil.

00:02:03.620 --> 00:02:07.060
The DMCA fails to account for the internet of today.

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:15.080
Instead of being used to protect the content creators that you watch and love, it's now being used to harass and even destroy those content creators.

00:02:15.080 --> 00:02:22.020
This is a chance for us to band together and protect the internet that we love, and bring it to the one place that can protect it as a whole.

00:02:22.020 --> 00:02:29.340
Until we get strict penalties in place for false DMCA takedowns- Youtube is always going to be under attack. And so will the internet.

00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:33.680
This is our chance to bring the fight out of Youtube and into Washington, DC.

00:02:33.680 --> 00:02:39.640
If you look below, Fight For the Future has created a website so that you can send comments to the government right now.

00:02:39.640 --> 00:02:41.400
